    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "> Since dev2p2 is described as Utilities to interact with nodes on the networking layer, without running a full blockchain\r\n\r\nI think you mean go-ethereum's cmd/devp2p here. It's a command-line tool for p2p protocol development and research.\r\n\r\nWe do not provide the kind of implementation you are asking about in go-ethereum, and also not here. In this repo here, we maintain only the *specifications* for network protocols. It's a place with information for people who implement the protocol. If you want to achieve this kind of light node, you need to implement it yourself using the specifications as a guide.",
